<h1>About The Program</h1>

<p>The DC Robotics program is amazingly different from most school programs in two main ways:  first, students don't have regularly-scheduled class time to work on and perfect their creations; and second, instead of a regimented curriculum commanding what to do, students are given a set of parts and encouragement.  This way, students come up with their own ideas, try them out, and succeed or fail&mdash;just like the real world.  Either way, students learn both how to build and problem-solve by doing.  If you're wondering how this could possibly lead to positive results, the DC teams consistently perform well, often winning tournaments and constantly hanging high in the rankings.</p>

